22:39.129 --> 22:42.254
And when I'm using it, I accidentally break it and I say, I'm so sorry.

22:43.135 --> 22:45.138
Let me buy you a new mug and you say, no, no, it's fine.

22:45.158 --> 22:47.802
And I go, no, let me get you a new mug.

22:47.842 --> 22:59.599
And the next morning, I show up and I have a full 12 piece dinner plate made of China with hundreds of pounds plates, bowls, mugs, platters, and I give it all to you.

23:00.861 --> 23:01.522
All matching.

23:02.754 --> 23:03.835
I haven't replaced the mug.

23:04.596 --> 23:05.617
I've overpaid for the mug.

23:06.979 --> 23:07.960
And that's what Jesus has done.

23:10.403 --> 23:11.604
It wasn't more than we needed.

23:11.965 --> 23:12.866
He doesn't say more.

23:13.086 --> 23:15.729
He says much more, way more.

23:17.471 --> 23:30.706
That grace and love, displayed on the cross through Jesus's obedience, which achieves our acceptance and relationship with Him, that's your weapon.

23:32.162 --> 23:32.763
to conclude.

23:34.366 --> 23:37.331
We should hold our thoughts at arm's length, interrogate them.

23:39.094 --> 23:41.599
The word of God is critical as a powerful tool.

23:43.402 --> 23:48.952
And our righteousness, giving to us through Christ's obedience, is our weapon.

23:51.276 --> 23:56.946
And this is only embraced when we have an understanding and acceptance in our hearts of God's love for us.

24:02.082 --> 24:03.086
So I'd love to respond.

24:03.567 --> 24:06.859
And it's easier if I could invite you if you're able to stand.

24:08.726 --> 24:09.970
So would you like to stand?

